main event: Four unidentified objects were observed in Alvion, California on 23/06/66 for a duration of 3.5 hours.
interesting points: The objects were white with red and green tints., The objects displayed erratic movements but generally remained in the same position., The sighting conclusion suggested the objects could be due to lighthouses., Photos taken during the observation were of poor quality., Witnesses included several individuals at the Point Cabrillo Light Station.
witness description: Mrs __________, boatswain mate 2nd Ronald Adams, engineman 2nd Carl Fullenwider, seaman Gary Carson, and a IC William E McOlusky all at Point Cabrillo Light Station.
